sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant Tekton as Tekton PipelineRun
    participant Git as Git Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Cachi2 as Cachi2 Prefetch
    participant AIPCC as AIPCC PyPI Index<br/>packages.redhat.com<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RPM as RPM Repositories<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Buildah as Buildah Build
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>quay.io / registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Dev,Registry: Flow 1: Workbench Image Build (Konflux)

    Dev->>Tekton: Trigger PipelineRun
    Tekton->>Git: Clone notebooks repo<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Git credentials
    Git-->>Tekton: Source code
    Tekton->>Cachi2: Prefetch dependencies
    Cachi2->>AIPCC: Fetch Python wheels<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Public (no auth)
    AIPCC-->>Cachi2: Python wheels (per-variant)
    Cachi2->>RPM: Fetch RPM packages<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Subscription certs
    RPM-->>Cachi2: RPM packages
    Cachi2-->>Tekton: /cachi2/output/deps/
    Tekton->>Buildah: Build image (hermetic)<br/>--no-index --find-links /cachi2/
    Buildah-->>Tekton: Built image
    Tekton->>Registry: Push image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Robot account
    Registry-->>Tekton: Push confirmed

    participant User as User Browser
    participant GW as RHOAI Gateway<br/>Envoy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant JL as JupyterLab / code-server<br/>8888/TCP or 8787/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Workbench Runtime (User Session)

    User->>GW: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3<br/>OpenID Connect
    GW->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer token
    KRBAC->>JL: Proxy to workbench<br/>HTTP/8888 or 8787<br/>Plaintext (pod-internal)<br/>No auth (trusted sidecar)
    JL-->>KRBAC: Response
    KRBAC-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>User: Workbench UI

    JL->>K8sAPI: Pipeline submission / K8s ops<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>JL: API response

    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant Manifests as Kustomize Manifests<br/>manifests/rhoai/base/
    participant Dash as RHOAI Dashboard

    Note over Operator,Dash: Flow 3: ImageStream Deployment

    Operator->>Manifests: Read kustomize manifests<br/>Filesystem / Git
    Manifests-->>Operator: ImageStream definitions
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Applied
    Dash->>K8sAPI: Query ImageStream API<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>User token
    K8sAPI-->>Dash: Available workbench images
